WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:11.211 --> 00:00:13.781
[ Tires screech ]
[ Crashing ]

2
00:00:19.787 --> 00:00:22.356
[ Flare sizzles ]

3
00:00:22.389 --> 00:00:24.659
[ Clattering ]

4
00:00:25.927 --> 00:00:28.563
[ "57 Coupe de Ville" plays ]

5
00:00:28.596 --> 00:00:32.399
♪♪

6
00:00:32.432 --> 00:00:35.068
♪ Well. everybody loves me ♪

7
00:00:35.102 --> 00:00:36.704
♪ Everywhere I go ♪

8
00:00:36.738 --> 00:00:38.540
♪ The women wanna kiss me ♪

9
00:00:38.573 --> 00:00:40.474
♪ The men all wanna know ♪
[ Spits ]

10
00:00:40.508 --> 00:00:42.042
♪ How's my baby handle ♪
[ Engine starts ]

11
00:00:42.075 --> 00:00:45.980
♪ When I take her up
to Blueberry Hill?

12
00:00:46.014 --> 00:00:47.549
[ Air hisses ]

13
00:00:47.582 --> 00:00:49.784
♪ I tell 'em
life's a bowl of cherries ♪

14
00:00:49.817 --> 00:00:53.420
♪ In my '57 Coupe de Ville ♪

15
00:00:54.989 --> 00:00:56.925
[ Music stops ]

16
00:00:56.958 --> 00:00:59.192
[ Wind howling ]

17
00:00:59.226 --> 00:01:02.429
[ Exhales sharply ]

18
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:10.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

19
00:01:12.239 --> 00:01:14.107
[ Engine shuts off ]

20
00:01:14.141 --> 00:01:16.209
[ Muzak playing ]

21
00:01:16.243 --> 00:01:18.613
[ Bowling pins clatter ]

22
00:01:21.516 --> 00:01:23.651
There he is.
Knew I'd get a handsome man

23
00:01:23.685 --> 00:01:25.352
in here if I waited around
long enough.

24
00:01:25.385 --> 00:01:27.354
Had to patch a tire
out on County Line.

25
00:01:27.387 --> 00:01:29.423
Too good for a tow?
Too impatient.

26
00:01:29.456 --> 00:01:32.627
You city folk.
Always in a hurry.

27
00:01:32.660 --> 00:01:34.227
By God. look who it is!

28
00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:35.964
He's back!
Hey!

29
00:01:35.997 --> 00:01:37.364
Welcome back. brother!

30
00:01:37.397 --> 00:01:38.800
Don't know why I ever leave.

31
00:01:38.833 --> 00:01:40.501
A place to bowl.
a place to fish.

32
00:01:40.535 --> 00:01:43.738
Together:
And a beer to hold doing it!

33
00:01:43.771 --> 00:01:45.205
[ Burps ]
[ Laughter ]

34
00:01:45.238 --> 00:01:46.473
Best friends!

35
00:01:46.507 --> 00:01:47.642
We love you. Ted!

36
00:01:47.675 --> 00:01:49.476
Together: Ted!

37
00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:57.451
♪♪

38
00:01:57.484 --> 00:02:04.993
♪♪

39
00:02:05.026 --> 00:02:13.433
♪♪

40
00:02:13.467 --> 00:02:21.174
♪♪

41
00:02:21.208 --> 00:02:23.410
You still selling PVC?

42
00:02:23.443 --> 00:02:24.879
How's -- How's
business down there?

43
00:02:24.912 --> 00:02:26.346
Good enough
to get me back up here.

44
00:02:26.380 --> 00:02:27.548
Think you could put in
a word?

45
00:02:27.582 --> 00:02:29.717
Son. you don't wanna
sell pipe.

46
00:02:29.751 --> 00:02:31.085
He just wants to lay some.

47
00:02:31.119 --> 00:02:32.352
[ Laughter ]

48
00:02:32.386 --> 00:02:34.689
Ah. good to have you back.
brother.

49
00:02:34.722 --> 00:02:36.624
Ahhh. Split a sixer?

50
00:02:36.658 --> 00:02:38.526
[ Engines starting ]

51
00:02:38.559 --> 00:02:40.628
Marjorie's keeping the place
open late now?

52
00:02:40.662 --> 00:02:43.230
Yeah. Her mother passed
a few months back.

53
00:02:43.263 --> 00:02:44.565
Don't think
she wants to go home.

54
00:02:44.599 --> 00:02:46.968
Everybody's runnin'
from something.

55
00:02:47.001 --> 00:02:49.236
[ Gearshift clicks ]

56
00:02:50.505 --> 00:02:52.006
[ Door opens. bottles clink ]

57
00:02:52.040 --> 00:02:54.075
How's Luisa?
She still kick you out of bed

58
00:02:54.108 --> 00:02:55.208
when you drink?
Yep.

59
00:02:55.242 --> 00:02:56.944
Might as well
keep drinking.

60
00:02:56.978 --> 00:02:58.579
[ Both laugh ]

61
00:02:58.613 --> 00:03:02.482
Open the register
and gimme your wallet!
[ Gasps ]

62
00:03:02.517 --> 00:03:03.618
Ahh!

63
00:03:03.651 --> 00:03:05.753
No. no. no.

64
00:03:07.789 --> 00:03:09.222
[ Robber groans ]

65
00:03:09.256 --> 00:03:10.958
[ Breathing heavily ]

66
00:03:10.992 --> 00:03:12.392
[ Clattering ]

67
00:03:12.426 --> 00:03:13.293
Teddy?

68
00:03:13.326 --> 00:03:14.696
Hello.
There's a robbery.

69
00:03:14.729 --> 00:03:16.564
I think this guy's having
a heart attack.

70
00:03:16.597 --> 00:03:18.800
[ Bells ring ]
Ted. where you going?

71
00:03:18.833 --> 00:03:20.968
Hey!
The cops are coming.

72
00:03:21.002 --> 00:03:22.235
Ted! Teddy!

73
00:03:22.269 --> 00:03:24.337
This guy's dying in here!

74
00:03:24.371 --> 00:03:26.841
[ Electricity humming ]

75
00:03:40.888 --> 00:03:42.023
Ahh!

76
00:03:42.056 --> 00:03:43.490
Gaaah!

77
00:03:43.524 --> 00:03:44.892
Alright. well. shit.
What the hell?
What the hell?!

78
00:03:44.926 --> 00:03:47.862
Looks like you learned
some things about your body.

79
00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:49.262
I'll make this simple. Ted.

80
00:03:49.296 --> 00:03:51.666
You're not a PVC salesman
from two states south.

81
00:03:51.699 --> 00:03:53.433
You're the smartest man
who's ever lived.

82
00:03:53.467 --> 00:03:55.368
and you were born
400 lightyears away.

83
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.138
You're on Beloi-6E.

84
00:03:57.171 --> 00:03:58.906
It's a primitive planet
with good country music

85
00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:02.009
and a shit-ton of snow.
real early '90s Earth vibes.

86
00:04:02.043 --> 00:04:03.611
They're 100 years
from first contact.

87
00:04:03.644 --> 00:04:06.180
so they don't know who I am --
who <i>you</i> are.

88
00:04:06.214 --> 00:04:07.447
Which is the whole point.

89
00:04:07.481 --> 00:04:09.282
Y-You think it's fun
to be a god. Ted?

90
00:04:09.316 --> 00:04:12.120
You think God's nipples get hard
when he murders a fish?

91
00:04:12.153 --> 00:04:13.353
Th-That's why every summer

92
00:04:13.386 --> 00:04:14.789
I take two weeks off
and come here.

93
00:04:14.822 --> 00:04:18.025
I wipe my brain and pull all
but my survival tech.

94
00:04:18.059 --> 00:04:20.628
[ Groaning ]

95
00:04:20.661 --> 00:04:22.997
I go home with the peace
of mind stupid people get

96
00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:24.732
from watching Kevin Costner
movies.

97
00:04:24.766 --> 00:04:27.668
So. look. if you're seeing this
because shit's gone sideways.

98
00:04:27.702 --> 00:04:29.402
hit the red button
to be me again.

99
00:04:29.436 --> 00:04:31.005
If everything's cool.
hit the blue button

100
00:04:31.038 --> 00:04:33.508
to clear this from your memory
and enjoy the rest of your trip.

101
00:04:33.541 --> 00:04:35.076
Okay. Morty. that's a wrap on

102
00:04:35.109 --> 00:04:36.677
"If you've been
messing with my tech."

103
00:04:36.711 --> 00:04:39.312
Let's run
the "Taken" scenarios.

104
00:04:39.781 --> 00:04:42.349
[ Groaning ]

105
00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:44.317
[ Gasps ]

106
00:04:44.351 --> 00:04:46.788
[ Breathing heavily ]

107
00:04:48.388 --> 00:04:50.658
[ Electricity zaps ]

108
00:04:55.563 --> 00:04:58.232
You here about
the dishwasher job?

109
00:04:58.266 --> 00:05:00.902
Shit. you're a popsicle.

110
00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:07.440
You know me. right?

111
00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:10.578
[ Chuckles ]
I'd sure like to think so.

112
00:05:10.611 --> 00:05:12.146
I mean it.
How could you?

113
00:05:12.180 --> 00:05:14.615
I'm just some guy
who shows up every year.

114
00:05:14.649 --> 00:05:17.585
Well. something keeps you
coming back here.

115
00:05:17.618 --> 00:05:20.320
Ooh! Lay back.
I got a surprise for you.

116
00:05:21.289 --> 00:05:23.456
Got this set up
since your last visit.

117
00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:25.593
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

118
00:05:25.626 --> 00:05:26.727
It's nice.

119
00:05:26.761 --> 00:05:28.930
Haven't really found occasion
to use it.

120
00:05:28.963 --> 00:05:30.598
Thanks for giving me one.

121
00:05:30.631 --> 00:05:33.034
I don't mind the company.

122
00:05:34.168 --> 00:05:36.070
You still have
that spare room in back?

123
00:05:36.103 --> 00:05:38.306
I don't want to sleep
in the RV.

124
00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:47.949
♪♪

125
00:05:49.382 --> 00:05:52.086
Mm. Don't go.

126
00:05:52.119 --> 00:05:54.454
I'm not gonna.

127
00:06:01.329 --> 00:06:02.964
[ Door opens ]

128
00:06:02.997 --> 00:06:05.733
Okay. obviously.
you're seeing <i>this</i> hologram

129
00:06:05.766 --> 00:06:08.236
because you ignored the
instructions from the last one.

130
00:06:08.269 --> 00:06:11.038
If you're seeing this hologram.
you decided to ignore...
I dunno why
that would've happened.

131
00:06:11.072 --> 00:06:12.573
it'd mean
you went pretty rogue.
...the hologram
that's currently playing.

132
00:06:12.607 --> 00:06:14.108
So just a gentle reminder --

133
00:06:14.141 --> 00:06:15.676
you're not a real person.
you're me.

134
00:06:15.710 --> 00:06:17.678
You're permanently...your
vacation spot.

135
00:06:17.712 --> 00:06:19.379
which hurts you more
than it hurts me.

136
00:06:19.412 --> 00:06:22.216
Though. in all honesty.
we're both getting hurt

137
00:06:22.250 --> 00:06:24.752
pretty severely...

138
00:06:26.453 --> 00:06:27.855
[ Laughter ]

139
00:06:27.889 --> 00:06:29.957
Ted. one of these days.
you gotta come up in July.

140
00:06:29.991 --> 00:06:33.393
I caught a muskie last summer
came about up to my neck.

141
00:06:33.426 --> 00:06:35.395
Stop lying to the man.
No fish in this lake.

142
00:06:35.428 --> 00:06:37.531
Actually. thought
I might stick around this year.

143
00:06:37.565 --> 00:06:39.432
See the thaw.
For real. Teddy?

144
00:06:39.466 --> 00:06:40.968
You're gonna --
You're gonna stay?

145
00:06:41.002 --> 00:06:42.303
What about your company?

146
00:06:42.336 --> 00:06:43.871
Doesn't seem real.

147
00:06:43.905 --> 00:06:47.241
I-It's like I've been pretending
I go somewhere when I leave.

148
00:06:47.275 --> 00:06:49.944
but I think I only exist
when I'm here.

149
00:06:49.977 --> 00:06:53.915
Like this is literally the
only place I'm actually alive.

150
00:06:55.249 --> 00:06:56.918
Does that...make sense?

151
00:06:56.951 --> 00:06:59.253
Good thing
nobody's driving tonight.

152
00:06:59.287 --> 00:07:01.822
[ Laughter ]

153
00:07:01.856 --> 00:07:04.158
[ Water splashes. reel squeals ]
Hey!

154
00:07:04.191 --> 00:07:06.994
[ Snoring ]

155
00:07:11.464 --> 00:07:14.101
[ Whirring ]

156
00:07:14.135 --> 00:07:22.143
♪♪

157
00:07:22.176 --> 00:07:25.212
[ Ringing ]

158
00:07:25.246 --> 00:07:27.715
Rick: Fuck me.

159
00:07:27.748 --> 00:07:29.550
Morty: <i>Hello? Rick? Rick!</i>
Who is this?

160
00:07:29.583 --> 00:07:31.152
<i>Aaawwww. I'm really gonna</i>
<i>get in trouble for this.</i>

161
00:07:31.185 --> 00:07:32.853
How are you calling
my leg?

162
00:07:32.887 --> 00:07:34.454
<i>I'm not supposed to ever</i>
<i>use the leg phone.</i>

163
00:07:34.487 --> 00:07:37.325
<i>but I-I just need you</i>
<i>to get in the egg.</i>

164
00:07:37.358 --> 00:07:39.060
<i>Don't pick a fight</i>
<i>with yourself. okay?</i>

165
00:07:39.093 --> 00:07:41.095
<i>I just want to get you home</i>
<i>before anything worse happens.</i>

166
00:07:41.128 --> 00:07:43.864
Nothing's worse than
finding out I'm some character

167
00:07:43.898 --> 00:07:46.200
that asshole plays.
some costume he puts on to --

168
00:07:46.233 --> 00:07:48.536
<i>He doesn't need you alive</i>
<i>to bring you home.</i>

169
00:07:48.569 --> 00:07:50.438
It's not my home!
I'm not him!

170
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.640
<i>You are.</i>
<i>I mean. I agree with you.</i>

171
00:07:52.673 --> 00:07:55.443
<i>He can be kind of a dick.</i>
<i>but y'know. this --</i>

172
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:57.178
<i>this is just how it is.</i>

173
00:07:57.211 --> 00:07:58.779
No! Help!

174
00:07:58.813 --> 00:08:01.349
Help!
<i>Oh. and if you could just</i>
<i>hang up the leg phone?</i>

175
00:08:01.382 --> 00:08:02.750
<i>I'll just -- I'll never</i>
<i>hear the end of it</i>

176
00:08:02.783 --> 00:08:04.652
<i>if the leg phone gets lost.</i>

177
00:08:04.685 --> 00:08:06.486
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

178
00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:08.488
[ Groaning ]

179
00:08:11.025 --> 00:08:12.492
Ted. are you okay?

180
00:08:12.526 --> 00:08:14.028
[ Groans ] Thank you.

181
00:08:14.061 --> 00:08:15.563
What is this thing. Ted?

182
00:08:15.596 --> 00:08:17.365
I'm not who you think I am.

183
00:08:17.398 --> 00:08:20.500
Is this your ship
from space?

184
00:08:20.534 --> 00:08:22.169
Your spaceship?

185
00:08:22.203 --> 00:08:23.371
It's his.

186
00:08:23.404 --> 00:08:25.373
He's...non-vacation me.

187
00:08:25.406 --> 00:08:27.641
I don't know him.
And I don't want to.

188
00:08:27.675 --> 00:08:29.210
But this asshole's
coming for me

189
00:08:29.243 --> 00:08:31.312
and I don't intend
to let him win.

190
00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:33.014
Marjorie:
For the love of Pete.

191
00:08:33.047 --> 00:08:34.882
Do you understand
what you're asking?

192
00:08:34.915 --> 00:08:37.618
I wouldn't ask at all
if there were any other way.

193
00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:41.989
<i>Janice. Mary.</i>
<i>I gotta send you home.</i>

194
00:08:42.023 --> 00:08:43.024
<i>We're closing early.</i>

195
00:08:43.057 --> 00:08:46.994
Come on!
We're only three frames in!

196
00:08:47.028 --> 00:08:48.662
[ Switches clicking ]

197
00:08:48.696 --> 00:08:50.798
Thank you.
[ Muttering ]

198
00:08:50.831 --> 00:08:52.833
Nobody gonna
take me seriously.

199
00:08:52.867 --> 00:08:54.835
Janice's gonna
have her word...

200
00:08:54.869 --> 00:08:57.506
Promise me you won't
come back here tonight.

201
00:08:57.538 --> 00:08:59.373
Always were dramatic.

202
00:08:59.407 --> 00:09:01.075
Promise.

203
00:09:01.108 --> 00:09:04.812
I just -- Don't die
in my bowling alley.

204
00:09:04.845 --> 00:09:07.014
You hear me?

205
00:09:09.316 --> 00:09:10.284
[ Groans ]

206
00:09:10.317 --> 00:09:12.353
[ Grunting ]

207
00:09:12.386 --> 00:09:13.687
Holy hell.

208
00:09:13.721 --> 00:09:15.456
How's it going out there.
Bowser?

209
00:09:15.489 --> 00:09:17.124
Bowser: All good.

210
00:09:19.528 --> 00:09:20.661
Sprinklers. Antonio?

211
00:09:20.694 --> 00:09:22.430
Working on it.
Little Mike?

212
00:09:22.463 --> 00:09:24.533
[ Valves squeaking ]

213
00:09:24.565 --> 00:09:26.434
[ Remote beeps ]

214
00:09:26.467 --> 00:09:28.302
Okay. Big Mike.

215
00:09:28.335 --> 00:09:29.437
[ Saw buzzing ]

216
00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:31.472
[ Rick screams ]

217
00:09:31.506 --> 00:09:34.075
[ Electricity humming ]

218
00:09:35.943 --> 00:09:38.112
[ Whoosh ]

219
00:09:39.013 --> 00:09:42.083
[ Whirring ]

220
00:09:44.218 --> 00:09:45.786
[ Drones buzzing ]

221
00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:47.955
Now!

222
00:09:56.964 --> 00:10:00.167
We need those sprinklers.
Antonio!

223
00:10:00.201 --> 00:10:02.537
It's not working.

224
00:10:02.571 --> 00:10:03.904
There's too many!

225
00:10:03.938 --> 00:10:06.107
Fry 'em!

226
00:10:09.376 --> 00:10:11.245
Mike!

227
00:10:12.379 --> 00:10:14.782
Follow me.
ya drone bastards!

228
00:10:15.850 --> 00:10:17.284
Whoa!

229
00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:20.555
Teddy. drop!

230
00:10:20.589 --> 00:10:22.123
[ Fire alarm rings ]

231
00:10:22.156 --> 00:10:24.191
[ Electronic whirring ]

232
00:10:27.661 --> 00:10:29.296
-Yes!
-Come on! Rack' em up!

233
00:10:29.330 --> 00:10:30.798
-Whoo-hoo!
-Time for a beer!

234
00:10:30.831 --> 00:10:32.900
Fuck you.
you self-centered prick!

235
00:10:32.933 --> 00:10:35.669
Who's not a real person now.
huh?

236
00:10:38.939 --> 00:10:40.575
Marjorie!

237
00:10:40.609 --> 00:10:42.176
Why'd you come back?

238
00:10:42.209 --> 00:10:43.911
I told you not to come back.

239
00:10:43.944 --> 00:10:45.713
You know me. [ Coughs ]

240
00:10:45.746 --> 00:10:47.982
I'm a stubborn old bitch.

241
00:10:48.015 --> 00:10:50.484
[ Coughs ]
Never could leave.

242
00:10:50.519 --> 00:10:52.686
[ Groans ]

243
00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:54.321
Ohh.
Oh. my God.

244
00:10:54.355 --> 00:10:56.957
I'm...sorry.

245
00:10:56.991 --> 00:10:59.727
[ Electricity zaps ]
Ah!

246
00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:02.029
Where you going.
Teddy?

247
00:11:03.831 --> 00:11:06.100
[ Electricity zaps ]

248
00:11:06.133 --> 00:11:07.835
[ Grunts ]

249
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:10.171
Ahh!

250
00:11:10.204 --> 00:11:13.407
[ Mechanical whirring ]

251
00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:14.975
Uh...Ted?

252
00:11:15.009 --> 00:11:17.077
He thought he could come here
and destroy me.

253
00:11:17.111 --> 00:11:19.648
so I'm gonna go there
and destroy him.

254
00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.081
Whattaya need from us?

255
00:11:21.115 --> 00:11:22.283
I need you to leave.

256
00:11:22.316 --> 00:11:23.684
I clearly can't keep you safe.

257
00:11:23.717 --> 00:11:25.219
I can't keep anyone safe!

258
